    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nNvim recognizes background by requesting terminal. Then it fires event OptionSet, but this event doesn't set `v:option_*` values, for example `v:option_new`. This breaks some commands that rely on new background value filled in `v:option_new`, like settings colorscheme based on background (see reproduction below).\n\nSeems like the following code has a problem: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/ad4bc2d90c5109c24bf6f0119ad31276f1518c6f/runtime/lua/vim/_core/defaults.lua#L939. It doesn't set option and so it doesn't fill these values. Instead it fires `OptionSet` event with the blank values. Looks like triggering `OptionSet` directly is error-prone.\n\nNvim v0.11 doesn't have this problem, because it sets option directly: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/v0.11.7/runtime/lua/vim/_defaults.lua#L810.\n\nWorkaround: read option value directly using `vim.o`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\n\ninit.lua:\n\n```lua\nlocal group = vim.api.nvim_create_augroup(\"sync_colorscheme\", { clear = true })\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"OptionSet\", {\n  group = group,\n  pattern = \"background\",\n  callback = function()\n    if vim.v.option_new == \"dark\" then\n      vim.cmd.colorscheme(\"habamax\") -- any dark theme.\n    else\n      vim.cmd.colorscheme(\"zellner\") -- any light theme.\n    end\n  end,\n})\n```\n\nI see light background. Print-debugging shows that `vim.v.option_new` is empty.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nDark theme, because my terminal is dark. Using workaround from problem description or Nvim v0.11 shows dark background.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-2727+gad4bc2d90c\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 26.4 (25E246)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.3.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color / xterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nwget https://github.com/neovim/neovim/releases/download/nightly/nvim-macos-arm64.tar.gz",
    "closed_at": null,
